      "description": "Available is a 1993 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine. This unit maintains excellent compression across all rotor faces, with the complex vacuum-actuated boost control system recently overhauled for seamless transition between primary and secondary turbochargers. The front-midship layout ensures a neutral polar moment of inertia, complemented by factory double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. The five-speed manual transmission exhibits precise gate engagement with no synchronizer grind. While the paint retains a driver-grade patina, the structural integrity of the chassis is uncompromised, and the cooling system has been upgraded with an aluminum radiator to manage thermal loads effectively. A purist-spec example ready for spirited driving.",
